title: Goodpasture, Father Ryan win state volleyball titles
text:
Goodpasture, Father Ryan win state volleyball titles Michael Murphy , mfmurphy@tennessean.com 2:49 p.m. CDT October 23, 2015 Buy Photo Goodpasture's Jennifer Rochelle dives to dig out a South Greene shot as Tatum Fox (22) looks on during Friday's Class A championship at MTSU. (Photo: Michael Murphy / The Tennessean) Buy Photo 
Class A: Goodpasture beats South Greene for Class A title 
Goodpasture claimed its fourth consecutive TSSAA state volleyball championship, capturing a 3-1 win over South Greene in Friday's Class A title match at Middle Tennessee State University. 
The Lady Cougars (45-11), who suffered a 3-1 setback to South Greene during Wednesday’s opening-round action, knocked off Lady Rebels 25-14, 15-25, 25-15, 25-21, 25-13 in Friday’s championship. 
Jennifer Rochelle, Jordan Jones and Lilly Dennison each tallied 10 kills for Goodpasture, while teammate Lou Phillips contributed 27 assists and 24 digs in the victory. 
More details coming soon. Buy Photo 
Father Ryan's bench reacts after the Lady Irish defeated Briarcrest 3-1 in the Division II-AA title match. (Photo: Michael Murphy / The Tennessean) 
DII-AA: Lady Irish win state volleyball title 
MURFREESBORO — The Father Ryan volleyball team defeated Briarcrest Christian 3-1 in Friday’s Division II-AA title match at Middle Tennessee State University, capturing the program’s first state championship since 2006. 
The Lady Irish (39-10), who fell to Baylor in last year’s title match, claimed a 25-22, 23-25, 25-14, 25-21 win over Briarcrest (45-5), which defeated the Irish 3-0 in Wednesday’s opening-round match. 
Senior Lauren Dorrell finished with a match-high 30 kills for Father Ryan, while teammate Maggie Thompson provided a team-leading 50 assists and seven digs.
